BOLU-OLU ESHO AKURE – A non-governmental organization, Artisan Headquarter, yesterday concluded a two-day training of auto mechanics and electricians in new technologies in Akure, Ondo state Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The training, which took place at Mechanic Village, Km 4, Ondo Road, Akure, was in two phases. Commenting on the training, some of the participants spoke with Daily Independent on their experiences. Oke Oluwafemi, an auto mechanic who participated, described the training as exciting and educative. He disclosed that he didn’t know anything about tracking device installation, but he’s now exposed to it. He said he would begin to do installation of tracking device in addition to his mechanic work.